b_{2k+1}
\frac{t}{1-e^{-t}} = \sum B_m \frac{t^m}{m!}.
k
x^k
\sum_{j=1}^n \frac{j^k x^k}{k!} = \sum_{j=1}^n e^{jx} = \frac{e^{(n+1)x} - e^x}{e^x-1}
= \left( \frac{e^{nx} -1}{x} \right) \left( \frac{x}{1-e^{-x}} \right) = \sum_{\ell=0}^{\infty} \frac{n^{\ell+1} x^{\ell}}{(\ell+1)!}  \cdot \sum B_m \frac{t^m}{m!}.
\sum B_m \frac{t^m}{m!} - \sum B_m \frac{(-t)^m}{m!} = \frac{t}{1-e^{-t}} - \frac{-t}{1-e^t} = \frac{t (e^t-1)}{e^t-1} = t.
